You could have the text in a regular rectangular div where the content flows normally, and then append a slight curvature afterwards with a `::after` pseudo element that is set to `position: absolute` and a couple pixels past the furthest distance right

[![Example][1]][1]

### Demo in Stack Snippets

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .list_item {
      height: 85px;
      width: 300px;
      background: white;
      border-radius: 25px;
      border: 1px solid black;
      margin-bottom: 5px;
      overflow: hidden;
      position: relative;
    }

    .circle {
        position: relative;
        box-sizing: border-box;
        height: 100%;
        padding: 0px 3px 0 10px;
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        background: #0000ce;
        color: white;
        max-width: 150px;
        z-index: 0;
    }

    .circle::after {
        content: &quot; &quot;;
        background: #0000ce;
        border-radius: 50%;
        width: 400px;
        height: 400px;
        position: absolute;
        z-index: -1;
